def initial_data_report(df):
    summary = {
        "shape": df.shape,
        "columns": df.columns.tolist(),
        "dtypes": df.dtypes.to_dict(),
        "missing_by_column": df.isnull().sum().to_dict(),
        "total_missing": df.isnull().sum().sum(),
        "duplicates": df.duplicated().sum()}
    return summary

def detect_column_types(df, unique_threshold=10, target_col="c"):
    categorical_cols = []
    numerical_cols = []

    for col in df.columns:
        if col == target_col:
            continue

        dtype = df[col].dtype
        unique_values = df[col].nunique()

        if dtype == 'object' or dtype.name == 'category':
            categorical_cols.append(col)
        elif dtype in ['int64', 'float64'] and unique_values <= unique_threshold:
            categorical_cols.append(col)
        elif dtype in ['int64', 'float64'] and unique_values > unique_threshold:
            numerical_cols.append(col)

    return {
        "categorical_cols": categorical_cols,
        "numerical_cols": numerical_cols
    }


def analyze_column(df, column, numerical_columns):
    print(f"\nAnalyzing Column: {column}")
    print("-" * 40)

    if column in numerical_columns:
        print("Type: Numerical")
        print(df[column].describe())

        fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 4))
        sns.histplot(df[column], kde=True, ax=axes[0], color='skyblue')
        axes[0].set_title(f'Histogram of {column}')

        sns.boxplot(x=df[column], ax=axes[1], color='lightgreen')
        axes[1].set_title(f'Boxplot of {column}')

        plt.tight_layout()
        plt.show()

    else:
        print("Type: Categorical")
        print(df[column].value_counts(dropna=False))

        plt.figure(figsize=(8, 4))
        sns.countplot(x=column, data=df, palette='pastel')
        plt.title(f'Countplot of {column}')
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
        plt.tight_layout()
        plt.show()


def analyze_dataframe(df):
    types = detect_column_types(df)
    numerical_columns = types["numerical_cols"]

    for column in df.columns:
        analyze_column(df, column, numerical_columns)


def corr_cols(df): 

    print("-" * 50)

    numeric_df= df.select_dtypes(include=["int64", "float64"])
    corr = numeric_df.corr(method="pearson")
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
    sns.heatmap(corr, annot=True, cmap="coolwarm", fmt=".2f", square=True)
    plt.title("Correlation Matrix pearson method", fontsize=16)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.yticks(rotation=0)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()



def correlation_with_target(df, target_col, method='pearson'):
    
    numeric_df = df.select_dtypes(include=['int64', 'float64'])
    
    corr = numeric_df.corr(method=method)[target_col].drop(target_col)
    
    sorted_corr = corr.reindex(corr.abs().sort_values(ascending=False).index)
    
    print(f"\n Correlation with target '{target_col}' (method: {method})")
    print(sorted_corr)
    
    return sorted_corr

def report_missing_values(df):
    
    total_rows = df.shape[0]

    miss_data=[]
    for col in df.columns:
        miss_count = df[col].isnull().sum()
        if miss_count > 0 :
            miss_percent = round((miss_count / total_rows) * 100, 2)
            miss_data.append({
                "Column": col,
                "Missing Count": miss_count,
                "Missing %": miss_percent
            })
    if miss_data:
        return pd.DataFrame(miss_data).sort_values(by="Missing %", ascending=False)
    else:
        print("No missing values found.")
        return pd.DataFrame(columns=["Column", "Missing Count", "Missing %"])

def manage_missing_values(df, categorical_cols):
    for col in df.columns:
        if df[col].isnull().sum() > 0:
            if col in categorical_cols:
                fill_value = df[col].mode()[0]
                df[col] = df[col].fillna(fill_value)
                print(f"{col}: missing values filled using mode ({fill_value})")
            else:
                fill_value = df[col].median()
                df[col] = df[col].fillna(fill_value)
                print(f"{col}: missing values filled using median ({fill_value})")

    return df

def checkdup(df) : 
    print("detecting duplicates...") 
    dups = df.duplicated().sum()
    print(f"number of duplicates rows: {dups} ")
    return dups

def removedups(df):
    print("removing dupliactes...")
    init = df.shape[0]
    df = df.drop_duplicates().reset_index(drop=True)
    print(f"removed rows : {init - df.shape[0]}")
    print(f"remained rows : {df.shape[0]}")
    return df

In[49]:
def distribution(df, column):

    print(f"\n Distribution Check {column}")
    stat, p = shapiro(df[column].dropna())
    print(f"   Shapiro-Wilk  stat: {stat:.5f}, p-value: {p:.5f}")
    dist_label = 'Normal' if p > 0.05 else 'Non-Normal'
    return dist_label, p

def manage_outliers(df, categorical_cols):
    print("\n Managing Outliers and Rare Categories\n")

    for col in df.columns:
        print("" * 60)
        print(f" Column: {col}")

        if col in categorical_cols:
            print(" Type: Categorical")
            value_counts = df[col].value_counts(normalize=False)
            rare_mask = value_counts < 0.05 * len(df)
            rare = value_counts[rare_mask]

            if not rare.empty:
                print(" Rare Categories Detected:")
                for k, v in rare.items():
                    percent = round((v / len(df)) * 100, 2)
                    print(f"   - '{k}': {v} rows ({percent}%)")

                df[col] = df[col].apply(lambda x: 'Other' if x in rare else x)
                print(" Action: Replaced rare categories with 'Other'")
            else:
                print(" No rare categories found.")

        else:
            print(" Type: Numerical")

            dist, p_val = distribution(df, col)
            print(f" Distribution: {dist} (Shapiro p = {p_val:.5f})")

            if dist == 'Normal':
                z_scores = (df[col] - df[col].mean()) / df[col].std()
                outlier_mask = abs(z_scores) > 3
            else:
                Q1 = df[col].quantile(0.25)
                Q3 = df[col].quantile(0.75)
                IQR = Q3 - Q1
                lower = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
                upper = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR
                outlier_mask = (df[col] < lower) | (df[col] > upper)

            count = outlier_mask.sum()
            print(f" Outliers Detected: {count}")

            if count > 0:
                low_clip = df[col].quantile(0.05)
                high_clip = df[col].quantile(0.95)
                df[col] = df[col].clip(lower=low_clip, upper=high_clip)
                print(f" Action: Clipped values to 5th95th percentiles")
            else:
                print(" No clipping needed.")

    print("" * 60)
    print(" Finished managing outliers.\n")
    return df

In[51]:
def encode_categorical_columns(df, categorical_cols, drop_first=True):

    print("Starting One-Hot Encoding...\n")

    dfEncoded = pd.get_dummies(df, columns=categorical_cols, drop_first=drop_first)

    new_columns = [col for col in dfEncoded.columns if col not in df.columns]

    print("One-hot encoding applied.")
    print(f" {len(categorical_cols)} categorical columns encoded.")
    print(f" {len(new_columns)} new columns created.\n")

    print(" Encoded Columns:")
    for col in categorical_cols:
        print(f" - {col}")

    print("\n New Columns Created:")
    for col in new_columns:
        print(f" + {col}")

    return dfEncoded

def prepare_data(df, target_col, numerical_cols, test_size=0.2, random_state=42):
    """
    Split data, scale numerical features, and apply SMOTE on training set.
    Returns X_train_scaled, X_test_scaled, y_train_resampled, y_test, scaler
    """
    
    print("\n Splitting data into train/test sets...")
    X = df.drop(columns=[target_col])
    y = df[target_col]

    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(
        X, y,
        test_size=test_size,
        random_state=random_state,
        stratify=y
    )

    print(f"   Train shape: {X_train.shape}")
    print(f"   Test shape : {X_test.shape}")

    # Step 1: Scale numerical features using StandardScaler
    print("\n Scaling numerical features using StandardScaler...")
    scaler = StandardScaler()
    X_train_scaled = X_train.copy()
    X_test_scaled = X_test.copy()

    X_train_scaled[numerical_cols] = scaler.fit_transform(X_train[numerical_cols])
    X_test_scaled[numerical_cols] = scaler.transform(X_test[numerical_cols])

    print(f"   Scaled {len(numerical_cols)} numerical features.")
    
    # Step 2: Apply SMOTE on training set
    print("\n  Handling class imbalance using SMOTE...")
    smote = SMOTE(random_state=random_state)
    X_train_resampled, y_train_resampled = smote.fit_resample(X_train_scaled, y_train)

    print("   Class distribution after SMOTE:")
    print(pd.Series(y_train_resampled).value_counts(normalize=True) * 100)

    # Plot distribution
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 4))
    sns.countplot(x=y_train_resampled, palette='pastel')
    plt.title("Class Distribution After SMOTE")
    plt.ylabel("Count")
    plt.xlabel("Class")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

    return X_train_resampled, X_test_scaled, y_train_resampled, y_test, scaler

def train_and_evaluate_models(X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test):
    """
    Train and evaluate multiple classifiers and compare their performance.
    """
    models = {
        "Logistic Regression": LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, random_state=42),
        "Random Forest": RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=100, random_state=42),
        "K-Nearest Neighbors": KNeighborsClassifier(),
        "Support Vector Machine": SVC(probability=True, random_state=42),
        "Decision Tree": DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=42),
        "XGBoost": xgb.XGBClassifier(use_label_encoder=False, eval_metric='logloss', random_state=42),
        "Neural Network": MLPClassifier(hidden_layer_sizes=(100,), max_iter=300, random_state=42)
    }

    results = []

    for name, model in models.items():
        print(f"\n Training: {name}")
        model.fit(X_train, y_train)
        y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
        y_prob = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]

        acc = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)
        prec = precision_score(y_test, y_pred)
        rec = recall_score(y_test, y_pred)
        f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_pred)
        auc = roc_auc_score(y_test, y_prob)

        results.append({
            "Model": name,
            "Accuracy": acc,
            "Precision": prec,
            "Recall": rec,
            "F1 Score": f1,
            "AUC": auc
        })

        print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred))

        # Confusion Matrix
        plt.figure(figsize=(5, 4))
        sns.heatmap(confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred), annot=True, fmt="d", cmap="Blues")
        plt.title(f"Confusion Matrix - {name}")
        plt.xlabel("Predicted")
        plt.ylabel("Actual")
        plt.tight_layout()
        plt.show()

    # Plot all ROC curves in one figure
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    for result in results:
        name = result["Model"]
        model = models[name]
        y_prob = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]
        fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_test, y_prob)
        plt.plot(fpr, tpr, label=f"{name} (AUC = {roc_auc_score(y_test, y_prob):.2f})")

    plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], linestyle='--', color='gray')
    plt.xlabel("False Positive Rate")
    plt.ylabel("True Positive Rate")
    plt.title("ROC Curves")
    plt.legend(loc="lower right")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

    # Summary Table
    results_df = pd.DataFrame(results)
    print("\n Final Model Comparison:")
    display(results_df.sort_values(by="F1 Score", ascending=False).reset_index(drop=True))

    #  Save results for later comparison
    results_df.to_csv("model_results.csv", index=False)

    return results_df

def optimize(X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test):
    """
    Optimize and evaluate models using GridSearchCV.
    """
    models = {
        "Logistic Regression": LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000),
        "Random Forest": RandomForestClassifier(random_state=42),
        "XGBoost": xgb.XGBClassifier(use_label_encoder=False, eval_metric='logloss', random_state=42),
        "Neural Network": MLPClassifier(random_state=42),
        "K-Nearest Neighbors": KNeighborsClassifier(),
        "Decision Tree": DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=42),
        "Support Vector Machine": SVC(probability=True, random_state=42)
    }

    model_params = {
        "Logistic Regression": {"C": [0.1, 1, 10], "solver": ["liblinear", "lbfgs"]},
        "Random Forest": {"n_estimators": [50, 100,200,300], "max_depth": [None, 10, 20]},
        "XGBoost": {"n_estimators": [50, 100], "learning_rate": [0.01, 0.1], "max_depth": [3, 5]},
        "Neural Network": {
            "hidden_layer_sizes": [(50,), (100,), (100, 50)],
            "activation": ['relu', 'tanh'],
            "learning_rate_init": [0.001, 0.01],
            "max_iter": [500],
            "solver": ['adam', 'sgd']
        },
        "K-Nearest Neighbors": {"n_neighbors": [3, 5, 7], "weights": ["uniform", "distance"]},
        "Decision Tree": {"max_depth": [None, 10, 20], "criterion": ["gini", "entropy"]},
        "Support Vector Machine": {"C": [0.1, 1], "kernel": ["linear", "rbf"]}
    }

    optimized_models = {}
    
    for name, model in models.items():
        print(f"\n Optimizing {name}...")
        grid = GridSearchCV(model, model_params[name], cv=5, scoring='accuracy', n_jobs=-1)
        grid.fit(X_train, y_train)
        best_model = grid.best_estimator_
        print(f" Best Params for {name}:", grid.best_params_)
        optimized_models[name] = best_model

    return optimized_models

from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve

def plot_roc_curve(y_true, y_score, label=None):
    fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_true, y_score)
    plt.plot(fpr, tpr, label=label)
    plt.xlabel("False Positive Rate")
    plt.ylabel("True Positive Rate")
    plt.grid(True)

def cross_validate_and_evaluate(models_dict, X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test):
    """
    Evaluate each optimized model with cross-validation and final test.
    """
    cv = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=5, shuffle=True, random_state=42)
    results = []

    for name, model in models_dict.items():
        print(f"\nCross-validating {name}...")
        pred_cv = cross_val_predict(model, X_train, y_train, cv=cv)
        prob_cv = cross_val_predict(model, X_train, y_train, cv=cv, method='predict_proba')[:, 1]

        # Cross-Validation F1
        f1_cv = f1_score(y_train, pred_cv)
        print(f" Mean F1 Score (CV): {f1_cv:.3f}")

        model.fit(X_train, y_train)
        y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
        y_prob = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]

        acc = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)
        prec = precision_score(y_test, y_pred)
        rec = recall_score(y_test, y_pred)
        f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_pred)
        auc = roc_auc_score(y_test, y_prob)

        results.append([name, acc, prec, rec, f1, auc])
        plot_roc_curve(y_test, y_prob, name)

    plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], linestyle='--', color='gray')
    plt.title("ROC Curve - Optimized Models")
    plt.legend()
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

    return results
'======================================================================================='
def display_optimized_results(results_list):

    df = pd.DataFrame(results_list, columns=["Model", "Accuracy", "Precision", "Recall", "F1 Score", "AUC"])
    df_sorted = df.sort_values(by="F1 Score", ascending=False).reset_index(drop=True)
    print("\n Summary of Optimized Models:")
    display(df_sorted)
    df_sorted.to_csv("optimized_model_results.csv", index=False)
    return df_sorted
